# Project Overview

This is an Elm-based project for motorsport analysis organized as a monorepo:

1. `app` - Frontend application (Elm and elm-pages)
2. `package` - Core Elm packages for data analysis and visualization
3. `cli` - Command-line tools for data processing
4. `review` - Elm review rules

## Technology Stack

- [Elm](https://elm-lang.org/) (0.19.1) for frontend and core logic
- [elm-pages](https://elm-pages.com/) for the web application
- TypeScript/JavaScript for tooling
- Vite for building

## Main Entry Points

- App: [app/index.ts](mdc:app/index.ts)
- Package: [package/src/DataView.elm](mdc:package/src/DataView.elm)
- CLI: [cli/src](mdc:cli/src)

## Project Architecture

The application follows a modular architecture:
1. Raw motorsport data is processed by CLI tools
2. Core data models and visualization components in the package
3. Frontend application consumes and displays the data
